** MEC Mining is a global mining consultancy specialising in mine planning, onsite management and technical services solutions for the international mining industry. **   
  
Solidify your portfolio of mining experience across a diverse range of
projects with MEC Mining!  
  
We are currently seeking ** Principal Geotechnical Engineer in both Open Cut
and/or Underground. **  
  
Reporting to the Manager of Geotechnical Services, you will work as a
Principal Geotechnical Engineer to provide geotechnical support for our
clients both locally and internationally.  
  
** Key Responsibilities: **   

  * Leading geotechnical studies for mining operations, to ensure geotechnical risks are effectively identified, managed and controlled 
  * Overseeing geotechnical input into both short & long-term production planning and scheduling processes 
  * Data analysis, geotechnical design and continuous improvement activities 
  * Providing guidance to the engineering team responsible for the day-to-day operations, including open pit or underground assessments when/where required 
  * Developing and mentoring junior engineers 
  
** Qualifications & Experience: **   

  * A degree in Civil/Geotechnical/Mining Engineering or Geology is required with relevant post graduate education relating to Geomechanics or Geotechnical Engineering (essential) 
  * RPEQ and AusIMM (CP) preferred 
  * At least 15 years design and site operational experience in a geotechnical engineering role within the resource sector. 
  * Preferably both Open Pit and Underground experienced, with various mining methods, backfill and geotechnical conditions 
  * Capability with geotechnical engineering software (i.e. Vulcan, Deswik, Rocscience suite and Map3D) 
  
** Personal Attributes: **   

  * Demonstrated ability to communicate effectively with a variety of stakeholders including management, technical professionals and operational personnel at all levels 
  * The drive to become a consultant an expert in your field 
  * Previous track record in building credibility within the local mining industry 
  * Excellent interpersonal and technical report writing skills 
  * Strong analytical ability and strategic capability 
  
